THAT'S WHAT SHEETS SAID:
Please take the time to be present for those you care about.  All to often, I find myself looking at my phone, thinking about myself, and not being engaged there for those around me.  We don't know when this part of the race we call life is going to end - for us or for our loved ones.  Focus on what is important (not ourselves) because you never really know how many opportunities you will have.  Each one is a gift (that's why it's called the present).

THAT'S WHAT SHEETS SAID:
This past weekend, I had the opportunity to volunteer with my son at the Idaho Foodbank with a great group of PAX ant their families and had a great time.  I am inherently a selfish person (not that I want to be, but there is no denying it).  Doing things to focus on others instead of myself helps me in my pursuit of happiness, and is something important to teach my kids.  I encourage all of us to continue to find ways to put others first (volunteering, Qing, etc.) because it will benefit both others and you.  

COT:  Yes, please and thank you.
From Hooch:  Life is precious, take the time to get things right with those close to you.  Don't let things remain unsaid, because you don't know how long you will have to say them.  Let people know you love them.

It was an honor to be with all of you PAX in the gloom this morning.  Thank you for pushing me!

‚Ä¢ Lilo Knee

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
Thanks for allowing me to try something new this AM, Gentlemen. While some improvements will be made and reiterated, I think the intention was fulfilled - carrying and sharing the load of life. 

Never forget that you are not in this alone. You may not always ask for it, nor do you need to. Sometimes, it falls on us to simply come along side and encourage/aid our fellow man. Even when the burden is ours to carry, we can learn to share parts and lean on others with more intention.

Be present. Be observant. Give love. Receive love. Practice sharing and shouldering.

YHC - Ax3

title: GTE training
moleskine:
*WARMUP:* None (we were at the DD)

*THE THANG:*
50lb+ rucks with SB, header over to a table.
4 PAX at a table, the other 3 were carrying SB.

Started out with table having 4 SB on top, so other 3 SB were carried by the others not on the table.

Carried the table around bellagio. Alternating PAX on which 4 were carrying the table. Eventually removing the SB off the table, so the other PAX were carrying double SB or sometimes triple SBs.

Ended the loop with 2 PAX carrying the table, with rest of the PAX carrying the rest of the SB.

Next phase: Canuck with his ruck was laying on the table, and the other 6 carried the table across the field. We successfully gently put it down. haha. Then 5 PAX pushed the table back with Freighter on the way back. 

4 PAX carried Puff across the field, 3 PAX carried Freighter back.

Grab all gear and headed back to cars.
